00:51.835 --> 00:55.100
With the Indians!

01:32.542 --> 01:33.770
Avram !

02:20.089 --> 02:22.250
I want to talk to you in private.

02:23.693 --> 02:25.593
Speak only English.

02:26.529 --> 02:30.226
And no matter what I say, don't smile.

02:42.212 --> 02:46.740
Out of 88 students graduating
from this yeshiva...

02:47.250 --> 02:49.912
you came in a close 87.

02:52.822 --> 02:53.811
Don't smile.

02:56.159 --> 02:57.524
Look sad.

03:00.563 --> 03:02.531
There is a new congregation...

03:02.599 --> 03:03.623
In America?

03:03.700 --> 03:05.065
Wait!

03:16.913 --> 03:20.849
<i>Some meshuggener suggested your
name to become the new rabbi.</i>

03:22.752 --> 03:26.711
I am forced to take an official
vote of the board of rabbis.

03:58.988 --> 03:59.977
Close.

04:01.157 --> 04:02.624
It's a close vote.

04:04.193 --> 04:06.184
But I am the Chief Rabbi!

04:07.030 --> 04:09.498
I am the one who has to decide!

04:10.533 --> 04:12.057
So, cowboy...

04:13.303 --> 04:16.567
I am sending you to San Francisco.

04:19.475 --> 04:21.807
- Where is San Francisco?
- By New York.

04:31.554 --> 04:33.112
Get out, quick.

04:42.265 --> 04:46.964
<i>And so, on a wonderful
sunny day in 1850...</i>

04:47.036 --> 04:50.199
<i>I started out my great adventure...</i>

04:50.273 --> 04:53.538
<i>and I left Poland for Philadelphia...</i>

04:53.609 --> 04:57.101
<i>the city where all the
brothers love each other...</i>

05:41.257 --> 05:42.849
The boat's gone.

05:47.630 --> 05:48.961
Understand?

05:49.032 --> 05:50.465
Somebody should have told us!

05:50.533 --> 05:51.625
This is the devil's work.

05:51.701 --> 05:53.362
- What'd he say?
- Says the boat is gone.

05:53.436 --> 05:55.870
Mister, what'd you just say
about the boat to San Francisco?

05:55.938 --> 05:57.030
- Gone!
- Well, that can't be.

05:57.106 --> 05:59.404
That boat's supposed to leave
first tide in the morning!

05:59.475 --> 06:00.806
Supposed to?

06:00.877 --> 06:02.640
What the hell's the matter with you?

06:02.712 --> 06:04.077
It's a gold rush.

06:04.213 --> 06:06.306
Haven't you people heard anything?

06:06.382 --> 06:08.873
- Next boat two months.
- Oh, God!

06:09.118 --> 06:10.881
Oh, my God, help me!

06:11.821 --> 06:14.449
Just this morning me and
my brother got the news.

06:14.524 --> 06:16.116
All right. Who's next?

06:21.364 --> 06:24.595
Our mama's dying in San Francisco.

06:25.334 --> 06:27.268
What am I gonna do?

06:27.437 --> 06:32.272
There must be some way that a
person can go to San Francisco...

06:32.341 --> 06:33.865
in another way than the boat.

06:33.943 --> 06:35.570
Not for us, sir.

06:35.912 --> 06:40.281
Just 10 minutes ago, me and my brother
sold our horses and our wagon...

06:40.349 --> 06:43.614
so as we could purchase
tickets on this here boat.

06:43.820 --> 06:46.345
And now we ain't got neither.

06:46.422 --> 06:48.913
Well, perhaps if you go to the man...

06:49.058 --> 06:51.822
and you told him your troubles
and you give him back the money...

06:51.894 --> 06:53.987
he would give you back the wagon.

06:54.797 --> 06:56.264
You think he'll do it?

06:56.332 --> 06:59.665
If he is a good man, I
think he would do that, yes.

06:59.735 --> 07:03.136
Mister, would you help me, please?

07:03.372 --> 07:06.307
I'm not much good at
explaining myself and...

07:06.676 --> 07:10.942
I usually just start to cry.

07:11.013 --> 07:12.344
I will do that.

07:12.415 --> 07:13.814
I would be happy to do it.

07:13.883 --> 07:16.249
But I don't know if I
would be much help to you.

07:16.319 --> 07:17.786
<i>With the way I speak English...</i>

07:17.854 --> 07:20.015
Wait, you don't have
to carry the bags.

07:20.089 --> 07:21.920
My brother, his name is Matt.

07:21.991 --> 07:24.152
- Oh, say, what's your name?
- Avram.

07:24.227 --> 07:26.195
Avram. My name's Darryl, Darryl Diggs.

07:26.262 --> 07:28.526
Anyway, my brother's got a temper.

07:28.598 --> 07:30.725
Sometimes he just unloads,
you know what I mean?

07:30.800 --> 07:32.734
- Can't I help you to carry...
- No, that's all right.

07:32.802 --> 07:34.326
I've got it all. Don't
worry about a thing.

07:34.403 --> 07:36.803
Just step in here, anyway. Come
on, what is it again, Avrum?

07:36.873 --> 07:39.273
Avram. But you didn't
do nothing wrong.

07:39.842 --> 07:42.811
- Everything go all right?
- Well, we missed the boat.

07:43.446 --> 07:45.414
- What?
- The boat sailed yesterday.

07:45.481 --> 07:49.349
The whole town's gone crazy, Matt.
It's gold rush. It sailed yesterday.

07:49.852 --> 07:51.649
Yeah, but what are
we supposed to do now?

07:51.721 --> 07:55.122
Well, God may be on our side yet,
Matt, thanks to this here gentleman.

07:55.391 --> 07:57.416
Avram, this is my
brother, Matthew Diggs.

07:57.493 --> 07:59.620
- How do you do?
- Mr. Jones!

08:00.429 --> 08:04.229
Mr. Jones, we missed our boat and we
find ourselves in a desperate state.

08:04.300 --> 08:05.824
We need our horses
and our wagon back...

08:05.902 --> 08:09.463
so as we can get to San Francisco
to see our mum before she dies.

08:09.672 --> 08:12.163
So if you'd be kind enough
to take your money back...

08:12.241 --> 08:15.642
I sympathize with your misfortunes,
fellows. But you've got to understand...

08:15.711 --> 08:18.236
I'm in the business of
buying and selling...

08:19.048 --> 08:21.744
and I don't sell unless
I can make a profit.

08:22.185 --> 08:24.710
But we don't have no
money to give you a profit.

08:24.787 --> 08:26.687
Then we don't do no business.

08:27.490 --> 08:30.721
Excuse me. Excuse me, Mr. Jones.

08:32.562 --> 08:36.498
How much profit do you
need from these gentlemen?

08:36.933 --> 08:38.423
$50.

08:38.668 --> 08:41.534
$50. That's it, Matt, we're sunk.

08:41.671 --> 08:44.139
I'm sorry, Avram. Sorry
I wasted your time.

08:44.740 --> 08:48.437
Well, perhaps I could pay the $50.

09:00.423 --> 09:02.357
It's real kind of you, Avram.

09:02.458 --> 09:05.757
I don't know how's we could
ever pay you back. Do you, Matt?

09:06.395 --> 09:09.193
$50, look, I don't know.

09:09.565 --> 09:12.193
If I could have a seat on
your wagon to San Francisco...

09:12.268 --> 09:14.259
I would be more than paid back.

09:14.537 --> 09:15.799
Well, you pay the $50...

09:15.871 --> 09:19.034
you could have a seat with a
cushion on it. Can't he, Matt?

09:19.542 --> 09:20.736
All the way.

09:21.277 --> 09:23.006
I would share the cushion.

09:24.413 --> 09:27.143
Matt, the Lord is smiling
on you and me today!

09:27.216 --> 09:28.342
Amen.

09:29.719 --> 09:31.346
Gentlemen, quiet!

09:32.221 --> 09:34.189
Wonderful, marvelous news.

09:35.591 --> 09:38.151
Just this morning, I
received this letter.

09:41.530 --> 09:43.589
"Dear Mr. Bender:

09:43.666 --> 09:47.329
"This is to inform you
that soon, God willing...

09:47.703 --> 09:50.433
"you will have a rabbi and a Torah.

09:56.178 --> 09:59.375
"Rabbi Avram Belinski
has left Poland...

09:59.448 --> 10:02.315
"to join you in the
village of San Francisco.

10:02.952 --> 10:06.410
"Avram thanks you for the
picture of your lovely family.

10:06.689 --> 10:11.251
"He is looking eagerly forward to
meeting your daughter Sarah Mindl...

10:11.327 --> 10:13.420
"with an eye towards matrimony."

10:15.231 --> 10:18.257
- Papa !
- Not now, Sarah Mindl.

10:19.435 --> 10:20.663
But, Julius!

10:21.637 --> 10:23.002
Go to your room.

10:23.406 --> 10:24.896
What's the matter with Sarah Mindl?

10:24.974 --> 10:28.603
Bender, a rabbi is
better than a Rosensheine.

10:45.428 --> 10:46.952
You want a bite?

10:47.029 --> 10:48.326
Oh, thanks.

11:05.581 --> 11:07.344
There she is, Avram.

11:07.483 --> 11:09.644
That little shortcut I
was telling you about.

11:09.719 --> 11:12.552
Gonna get us to San
Francisco four days earlier.

11:12.621 --> 11:13.645
Good.

11:52.528 --> 11:53.517
Whoa !

11:53.629 --> 11:55.529
What happened? Is it Indians?

11:55.598 --> 11:57.429
Mr. Jones, what's happening?

12:04.473 --> 12:06.600
<i>I don't understand. What's...</i>

12:06.675 --> 12:09.109
Darryl, tell him I paid the $50!

12:09.612 --> 12:11.273
He paid the $50.

12:11.447 --> 12:13.915
- You paid the $50?
- Yeah, I did.

12:22.158 --> 12:23.648
Is it clothes what you want?

12:23.726 --> 12:25.455
You want to take my clothes?

12:25.528 --> 12:28.463
You need my clothes so much?
You don't have your own clothes?

12:31.367 --> 12:34.461
No! No! Not the Torah, please!

12:34.537 --> 12:36.505
<i>Take my money, you can have the...</i>

12:36.572 --> 12:39.097
God! God, help me!

12:39.241 --> 12:41.471
Mr. Jones, please don't do that!

12:44.814 --> 12:48.181
Please! Please! No!

12:48.250 --> 12:50.218
What's you need my tallis for?

12:53.322 --> 12:55.051
Why are you doing this?

12:55.124 --> 12:56.421
- We love you.
- Mr. Jones...

12:56.492 --> 12:58.357
why are you doing this?

12:58.427 --> 13:00.793
- You're not happy with our service?
- No.

13:04.600 --> 13:09.264
God! I don't want to be
with these filthy crooks!

13:09.338 --> 13:12.000
- We'll fix that for you, bucko.
- No!

13:12.074 --> 13:13.541
There you go!

13:27.590 --> 13:30.491
- How'd we do?
- I got the rest of his money.

16:32.174 --> 16:34.665
This you couldn't throw out first!

16:58.067 --> 16:59.159
America.

17:34.036 --> 17:36.630
Landsmen! Landsmen!

17:36.805 --> 17:38.238
Hello!

17:39.708 --> 17:41.107
Landsmen!

17:42.277 --> 17:43.266
Landsmen!

17:43.445 --> 17:44.605
Hello!

17:46.281 --> 17:47.578
Landsmen!

18:23.986 --> 18:26.511
Dost thou speak English?

18:29.725 --> 18:31.215
Dost thou...

18:32.895 --> 18:34.795
<i>speak...</i>

19:22.978 --> 19:25.173
You know, I think he's crazy.

20:17.766 --> 20:19.256
We have decided...

20:19.601 --> 20:23.367
that thou shouldst have this
money for the train to Akron.

20:28.744 --> 20:31.269
We are sorry it cannot be more.

20:33.315 --> 20:37.479
We all hope it will help
thee on thy journey...

20:38.086 --> 20:39.485
Brother Avram.

20:45.928 --> 20:50.524
I will never forget thy kindness.

20:53.402 --> 20:54.596
Thanks.

21:07.249 --> 21:10.878
Bye-bye.
Good-bye, children.

21:12.921 --> 21:16.516
Good-bye. Thank you very much.

21:17.559 --> 21:18.617
Thanks.

21:18.694 --> 21:22.095
- Good-bye. -
Good-bye, Avram.

21:24.666 --> 21:26.759
My parents have a farm...

21:26.835 --> 21:30.601
not big like this one,
but they have a nice farm.

21:31.273 --> 21:33.503
How is it that thou are not a farmer?

21:34.776 --> 21:36.835
Well, God made me a rabbi.

21:37.579 --> 21:39.843
- Why?
- Why?

21:41.616 --> 21:44.107
I think he had enough farmers.

21:47.889 --> 21:49.914
What a wonderful country.

22:12.247 --> 22:15.683
Simple Simon says, "Put
your fingers on your nose."

22:18.020 --> 22:20.511
Simple Simon says, "No laughing."

22:21.757 --> 22:25.887
Simple Simon says, "Put
your fingers on your nose."

22:26.395 --> 22:28.158
I really have to go!

22:30.332 --> 22:33.529
Simple Simon says, "Put
your fingers on your nose."

22:35.337 --> 22:37.237
Don't bother the man, honey.

22:39.007 --> 22:42.204
Simple Simon says, "You
don't have to play."

22:49.317 --> 22:51.615
I think we're an hour and a half away.

23:41.036 --> 23:44.494
- Mommy, I'm getting sleepy.
- Then take a nap.

24:25.080 --> 24:27.674
- Can you stop it?
- Mama, I'm hungry.

25:10.125 --> 25:13.561
Ladies and gentlemen, can I
have your attention, please?

25:13.762 --> 25:15.525
Now I want you all to
stay calm and listen...

25:15.597 --> 25:17.565
'cause I'm only gonna say this once.

25:19.000 --> 25:21.628
First thing is: don't turn around.

25:22.270 --> 25:24.397
There's a man behind
you with a big shotgun...

25:24.472 --> 25:26.633
and he don't care to be recognized.

25:27.842 --> 25:30.538
Them that don't
believe me is gonna die.

25:32.247 --> 25:35.808
All right now. You all put
your hands on top of your heads.

25:36.518 --> 25:38.918
Good. That's real good.

25:39.754 --> 25:42.484
Now we're all gonna play
like we're in church.

25:43.258 --> 25:45.317
You got something for
the collection, sir?

25:46.194 --> 25:47.422
Very kind.

25:48.363 --> 25:50.558
Ma'am? Thank you.

25:50.632 --> 25:52.463
Thank you very much.

25:52.601 --> 25:53.590
Ma'am?

25:59.741 --> 26:00.833
Thank you.

26:01.776 --> 26:03.937
Well, thank you all very much.

26:04.012 --> 26:06.810
Mr. Jake, I'm jumping here,
you go at the next bend.

26:07.215 --> 26:08.682
Remember, folks...

26:08.750 --> 26:12.117
the best way to keep your heads
is keep your hands on top of them.

26:12.187 --> 26:13.779
And don't turn around.

26:14.990 --> 26:17.891
Better to give than to
receive, ain't it, folks?

27:14.049 --> 27:18.577
Simple Simon says, "Everybody laugh."

27:27.562 --> 27:29.427
Don't you get the joke?

27:29.497 --> 27:33.593
Simple says, "Everybody gotta laugh."

28:32.494 --> 28:37.022
<i>It's difficult to explain that
a Jew can't ride on a Saturday.</i>

28:37.465 --> 28:41.492
<i>And, for a Jew, Saturday
begins on Friday.</i>

28:43.304 --> 28:45.135
- Name?
- Joseph Pellerton.

28:48.376 --> 28:50.310
See the foreman. Name?

28:51.946 --> 28:53.811
Good? Good.

28:55.884 --> 28:58.546
See the foreman. Name?

28:58.620 --> 28:59.985
You funny looking fellow.

29:00.555 --> 29:03.752
- Yes. Yes.
- See the foreman. Name?

29:04.592 --> 29:05.684
Yes.

29:07.462 --> 29:08.520
See the foreman.

29:08.596 --> 29:12.032
- You ever work on railroad before?
- No. This is the first time for me.

29:12.100 --> 29:13.089
<i>K-O-V...</i>

29:16.037 --> 29:17.026
See the foreman.

29:17.105 --> 29:19.096
- You sure talk funny.
- Name?

29:22.277 --> 29:23.471
- Yes.
- See the foreman.

29:23.545 --> 29:24.569
- Yes.
- Name?

29:24.646 --> 29:25.635
John Browning.

29:25.713 --> 29:27.977
Strange-looking characters
looking for jobs.

29:28.049 --> 29:29.448
See the foreman.

29:30.151 --> 29:31.641
- Name?
- Belinski.

29:47.702 --> 29:50.933
Sorry, Paco. Sorry. It
wouldn't happen again.

29:51.272 --> 29:53.900
You can bet your boots on that.

30:06.921 --> 30:08.218
He did it again.

30:22.270 --> 30:24.795
Wait, Paco. Wait!

30:25.139 --> 30:27.164
Wait, it wasn't done on purpose.

30:27.742 --> 30:31.075
- Avram, some water over here.
- Coming right up.

30:31.346 --> 30:34.110
Got nice, fresh water coming right up.

30:34.682 --> 30:37.480
- Avram.
- What? What happened?

30:37.685 --> 30:39.812
Paco? No!

30:39.888 --> 30:43.619
<i>- It was an accident. I didn't mean to...
- I kill you, pendejo!</i>

30:43.691 --> 30:45.522
I'll bust your Jewish bones!

30:45.994 --> 30:49.088
You smart, you listen.
We open a big restaurant.

30:49.163 --> 30:51.688
You work one year, make
enough money to buy a wagon.

30:51.766 --> 30:53.199
Maybe we even go with you, huh?

30:53.268 --> 30:55.361
Open a big joint in San Francisco!

30:55.436 --> 30:59.133
Paco, would you show
me where to buy a horse?

30:59.541 --> 31:02.669
<i>Hey, pendejo. How you
going to find your way?</i>

31:02.844 --> 31:07.076
Paco, please, just show
me where to buy a horse.

31:11.819 --> 31:16.586
You're crazy, Jew-boy!
You gonna get lost!

31:17.058 --> 31:21.154
Believe me, I won't get lost!

31:21.563 --> 31:24.259
Oh, yes, you will.

31:29.103 --> 31:30.331
Good-bye!

31:31.139 --> 31:33.107
Good-bye, Paco.

31:33.841 --> 31:36.173
Good-bye, Mr. Ping!

31:36.377 --> 31:39.346
Wait! Wait, horsie!

31:39.480 --> 31:41.778
Wait, wait, horsie! Take it easy.

31:42.584 --> 31:46.577
Nice horsie. That's a good horsie.

31:46.688 --> 31:47.780
That's it.

31:48.089 --> 31:50.216
Let's take it slow and easy.

31:51.225 --> 31:53.056
Slow! Slow.

31:53.561 --> 31:55.529
That's it. You're a good horsie.

31:55.597 --> 32:00.500
Sarah Mindl. Sarah, Sarah, Sarah.

32:02.270 --> 32:05.637
Oh, my Sarah, Sarah.

32:10.044 --> 32:13.207
Oh, show me what you meant to me.

32:30.732 --> 32:34.691
Oh, my food! My food!

32:44.212 --> 32:45.440
Why me?

32:45.513 --> 32:47.310
My food, you're gonna take?

32:47.448 --> 32:50.315
You got the whole world,
you're gonna take my food!

32:56.691 --> 32:58.158
Not you! Wait!

32:58.226 --> 33:01.457
Not you! Wait! Horsie, wait!

33:03.998 --> 33:05.932
No food and no horse.

33:08.569 --> 33:09.934
Come back!

33:10.004 --> 33:11.699
Come here, horsie!

33:11.773 --> 33:14.298
I'll be good to you! I'll be nice!

33:14.375 --> 33:16.343
I'll pick grass for you!

33:16.444 --> 33:18.275
I'll scratch your back!

33:18.346 --> 33:20.041
I'll give you a nice rub!

33:27.088 --> 33:29.921
Chicken, chicken.
Chickie, chickie, chicken.

33:29.991 --> 33:32.653
Come here. I don't wanna hurt you.

33:32.894 --> 33:34.691
I just want to eat you.

33:39.367 --> 33:42.427
Come here, wait! I
don't wanna hurt you!

33:42.637 --> 33:45.071
I just want to make you kosher!

34:28.483 --> 34:30.143
How hungry are you?

34:32.587 --> 34:34.248
I'm pretty hungry.

34:52.607 --> 34:54.734
If you had been here yesterday...

34:54.809 --> 34:56.777
we could've had roast chicken!

35:03.317 --> 35:05.251
So that's Jewish cooking, huh?

35:06.821 --> 35:08.311
Pretty good, huh?

35:10.858 --> 35:12.587
Where're you coming from?

35:13.995 --> 35:15.121
Back there.

35:16.364 --> 35:18.195
You're from California, huh?

35:22.837 --> 35:24.737
California is that way?

35:28.276 --> 35:30.073
You're lost, ain't you?

35:32.413 --> 35:35.041
- Got any money?
- No.

35:37.318 --> 35:38.910
Got any food?

35:40.254 --> 35:41.243
No.

35:46.460 --> 35:47.859
Sure talk funny.

35:47.929 --> 35:50.261
- Where you born at?
- Poland.

35:52.099 --> 35:54.590
Is that near Pittsburgh?

35:56.003 --> 35:57.994
No. That's near Czechoslovakia.

35:58.873 --> 36:00.306
Oh, yeah. Yeah.

36:02.944 --> 36:04.969
And you're going to California?

36:05.646 --> 36:06.704
Yes.

36:10.284 --> 36:11.979
You ain't gonna make it.

36:13.487 --> 36:14.749
Excuse me...

36:15.590 --> 36:17.888
in the morning, would
you be kind enough...

36:17.959 --> 36:21.190
to point out in which
direction is San Francisco?

36:22.296 --> 36:23.627
- Sure.
- Good.

36:24.799 --> 36:26.494
- In the morning.
- In that case...

36:26.901 --> 36:29.199
would you like to fight
for that last fish?

36:33.107 --> 36:34.301
You think you got a chance?

36:36.410 --> 36:41.347
I think I can say, with complete
confidence, none whatsoever...

36:42.583 --> 36:44.107
but I'm still hungry.

36:45.386 --> 36:47.616
- Help yourself.
- Thanks.

36:51.158 --> 36:53.058
What you call this kind of fish?

36:53.895 --> 36:56.955
- That's a trout.
- A trout?

36:58.366 --> 37:00.129
It's got a lot of bones.

37:03.337 --> 37:05.396
You got family waiting for you?

37:05.873 --> 37:08.967
I'm promised a wife when
I get to San Francisco.

37:09.043 --> 37:10.601
But I haven't never met her.

37:10.678 --> 37:13.738
You gonna marry a woman
that you never seen?

37:14.382 --> 37:16.316
I didn't say I never seen her.

37:16.384 --> 37:18.011
I said I never met her.

37:19.353 --> 37:23.016
They sent me a picture
before I left Poland.

37:29.430 --> 37:31.455
Well.

37:31.532 --> 37:32.658
What you think?

37:32.733 --> 37:34.360
Well, that's my kind of woman.

37:34.435 --> 37:35.800
You son of a gun.

37:36.537 --> 37:38.937
You son of a gun, you.

37:40.374 --> 37:41.636
Shee-it!

37:43.544 --> 37:44.875
I guess so.

37:45.112 --> 37:47.239
This other one ain't bad, neither.

37:50.151 --> 37:54.281
- Good night, Rabbi.
- Good night, cowboy.

38:14.809 --> 38:17.277
Well, it's nice meeting
up with you, pard.

38:17.411 --> 38:19.402
Nice meeting up with you, pard.

38:19.847 --> 38:21.838
- You got it straight?
- Oh, sure.

38:21.949 --> 38:23.507
Right from this tree...

38:23.584 --> 38:25.916
I head straight north
five or six weeks...

38:25.987 --> 38:28.012
till I come to the flat country.

38:28.255 --> 38:32.385
- Yeah.
- Then I make a left for two days.

38:32.460 --> 38:34.451
That way I avoid the Indians.

38:35.496 --> 38:37.191
Then I cross the river...

38:38.099 --> 38:41.296
and I make a sharp right,
away from the mountains.

38:43.404 --> 38:45.929
Once I get to the
desert, God willing...

38:46.273 --> 38:49.174
I just continue straight as piss...

38:49.377 --> 38:52.813
till I come to the
ocean. Take a left...

38:53.314 --> 38:55.782
keeping the ocean on
my right shoulder...

38:55.916 --> 38:58.908
and just hot-tail it
right into San Francisco.

39:00.254 --> 39:01.243
Good?

39:02.757 --> 39:03.917
Pretty good.

39:04.892 --> 39:05.881
Well...

39:07.495 --> 39:08.985
I hope you make it.

39:15.169 --> 39:20.163
Okay, wait, horse. Good.
All right, go, horsie.

39:20.975 --> 39:24.877
That's it, straight ahead.

39:28.482 --> 39:33.249
- Speak any Mexican, do you?
- No. Why do you ask?

39:34.555 --> 39:37.649
Oh, nothing. Just curious.

39:39.960 --> 39:44.727
If you should ever come to San Francisco,
I hope that you'll call on me...

39:44.965 --> 39:47.297
and we could talk
over some nice times.

39:53.674 --> 39:56.268
- Come on, horsie.
- Hey...

39:58.512 --> 39:59.979
that way.

40:01.982 --> 40:03.506
That way?

40:05.586 --> 40:07.747
Of course, I know it's that way...

40:08.022 --> 40:11.788
but first I have to go around that
big log before I can go that way!

40:12.093 --> 40:15.927
You mustn't turn a horse so
quick. That's how accidents happen.

40:16.330 --> 40:21.029
You gotta start nice and slow. That
way you get off on the right foot.

40:28.442 --> 40:32.742
Hey! What kind of crazy horses
they got in this country?

40:38.252 --> 40:42.245
<i>- What do you call this in Jewish?
- A tokhes.</i>

40:43.491 --> 40:47.655
<i>Well, you keep your eyes on this tokhes
and don't take them off till I tell you.</i>

40:48.696 --> 40:51.529
<i>Keep my eyes on the tokhes...</i>

40:58.739 --> 41:02.004
Shee-it! Don't get no
closer to that edge, Rabbi.

41:03.811 --> 41:06.245
- What kind of word is that?
- What word?

41:06.413 --> 41:08.973
You always say, "shee-it"
at a certain moment.

41:09.049 --> 41:10.448
Shee-it?

41:12.720 --> 41:16.019
<i>Well, that's a... That's a...</i>

41:16.323 --> 41:20.487
<i>What do you... You must have a
word in your language that you...</i>

41:22.196 --> 41:24.994
What do say when you get
really took by surprise?

41:25.366 --> 41:26.560
<i>Oy gevald.</i>

41:27.434 --> 41:28.423
<i>Oy gevald?</i>

41:28.769 --> 41:33.263
- Yeah. - That's it.
That's what "shee-it" means?

41:36.210 --> 41:37.802
<i>Oy, shee-it!</i>

41:39.046 --> 41:40.843
Yeah, that makes sense.

41:42.216 --> 41:44.844
Slow. Slow, horsie.

41:52.493 --> 41:54.324
Well, this is it.

41:55.696 --> 41:57.926
- Where are you going?
- Back down the river a few miles...

41:57.998 --> 41:59.488
it's a good place to cross.

41:59.833 --> 42:01.460
- Why not here?
- Here?

42:02.503 --> 42:03.800
Here's a good place to die...

42:03.938 --> 42:06.133
but it ain't a good
place to cross the river.

42:06.207 --> 42:10.473
We just jump in and swim
straight across. Simple as pie.

42:12.479 --> 42:14.310
You wanna kill yourself, go ahead.

42:14.381 --> 42:17.077
I don't like the odds.
I'm taking the long way.

42:25.859 --> 42:28.327
Well, that shouldn't be so difficult.

42:38.706 --> 42:42.267
Wait a minute! Where
you going, horsie?

42:42.509 --> 42:45.410
I didn't say where to go yet!

42:47.114 --> 42:48.843
Oh, no! Oh, no!

43:07.334 --> 43:08.995
That snake could've killed me!

43:09.536 --> 43:11.936
Well, damn me! If he
can do it, I can do it.

43:21.315 --> 43:23.715
<i>Help! Oy gevald!</i>

43:24.218 --> 43:25.207
God damn!

43:34.561 --> 43:35.960
Shit!

43:40.701 --> 43:44.137
You know, Rabbi, you're
one crazy bastard!

43:44.638 --> 43:45.627
Remember...

43:45.973 --> 43:50.273
I'm the kind of person when he says
he's gonna do something, he does it.

43:51.612 --> 43:54.809
You got a guarantee, huh? He could
be laying out there somewhere...

43:54.882 --> 43:57.510
- dead in the wilderness!
- Bite your tongue!

43:57.785 --> 44:00.253
You're talking about
my future son-in-law.

44:06.660 --> 44:10.357
Somebody, maybe, should
remind Sarah Mindl.

44:15.969 --> 44:17.334
Rosalie.

44:18.672 --> 44:19.661
Rosalie.

44:20.174 --> 44:24.543
- Get your sister away from that idiot!
- I'm not mixing in. I'm not mixing in.

44:26.880 --> 44:30.680
This is a nice little
town. Cold, but nice.

44:30.984 --> 44:33.214
Yeah, I guess.

44:34.121 --> 44:37.682
I don't think that fellow is 100%.

44:42.262 --> 44:44.526
I'll see if I can find
us some place to stay.

44:47.868 --> 44:51.463
- Someplace pretty cheap.
- Yeah, pretty cheap.

45:20.267 --> 45:21.393
<i>About tomorrow morning...</i>

45:23.070 --> 45:25.004
This ain't traveling weather.

45:25.339 --> 45:29.036
I know this place ain't
fancy, but it's got a roof.

45:29.877 --> 45:32.004
And like you say, it's cheap.

45:34.248 --> 45:36.648
So we just stay here for a
couple months and then head south.

45:36.717 --> 45:39.151
No. I've wasted too much time already.

45:44.725 --> 45:48.183
When they banged on your head,
they must've mushed your brains!

45:48.595 --> 45:52.395
So goddamned worried about time,
how come you don't ride on Saturday?

45:52.566 --> 45:55.729
I told you, it's against my
religion to ride on the Sabbath.

45:56.470 --> 46:00.770
I got me a new religion, too! And one of
the things you ain't allowed to do is die!

46:01.175 --> 46:05.043
There's real mountains out there, and
that's a real blizzard building up.

46:05.112 --> 46:08.240
- I'm telling you we can't make it.
- I can make it.

46:08.882 --> 46:13.876
God damn! I ain't gonna let you talk
me into this. It's just impossible!

46:14.154 --> 46:18.147
Every goddamn Indian knows that!
Every goddamn trapper knows that!

46:21.462 --> 46:24.226
I know, you don't like
it when I talk that way.

46:25.232 --> 46:29.293
But I'm telling you, you ain't
gonna talk me into it this time!

46:31.205 --> 46:34.197
Am I trying to talk you into anything?

46:38.812 --> 46:41.406
Good night! Have a nice trip.

46:42.216 --> 46:46.619
Good night. And thanks for
everything you did for me...

46:47.788 --> 46:50.916
up until the time I
needed you the most!

46:55.195 --> 46:57.095
Don't wake me in the morning!

46:58.999 --> 47:02.230
I'll try to be as quiet as possible!

47:04.938 --> 47:06.963
What do you think now, Rabbi?

47:07.608 --> 47:08.802
It's cold.

47:13.146 --> 47:14.977
You should see it in winter.

47:23.524 --> 47:27.654
<i>In the Talmud it says,
"Find thyself a teacher."</i>

47:28.462 --> 47:30.020
<i>And this I had done.</i>

47:34.668 --> 47:39.196
<i>However, there were times I feared
that he would find another pupil.</i>

47:42.743 --> 47:44.904
Get your horse down!

48:05.198 --> 48:08.429
If we'd have gone on,
we'd have froze to death!

48:09.636 --> 48:11.536
No, make one!

48:14.074 --> 48:17.441
Move! Come here...

48:20.447 --> 48:21.675
closer!

48:24.251 --> 48:25.275
Wait.

48:25.686 --> 48:29.122
We are doing this to
keep warm, aren't we?

48:30.123 --> 48:32.717
In that case, you can
put your arms around me.

48:35.295 --> 48:36.762
Come here, darling.

48:40.467 --> 48:42.025
That's better.

48:51.144 --> 48:52.975
Hey, look.

49:04.191 --> 49:06.682
I think we've found
the Garden of Eden.

49:07.094 --> 49:09.460
Well, it ain't exactly
the Garden of Eden.

49:13.600 --> 49:15.795
What a wonderful place America is!

49:16.303 --> 49:17.964
There are no walls
around these cities.

49:18.038 --> 49:20.734
You don't have to worry about soldiers
coming in from the next town...

49:20.807 --> 49:21.899
and killing people.

49:23.210 --> 49:25.610
You know, I think this is the West.

49:25.879 --> 49:30.248
We're in the Wild West here, just
like the books I read in Poland.

49:31.284 --> 49:35.744
This is a wonderful city. They
got banks and restaurants...

49:36.857 --> 49:41.021
they got merchants of all kinds
here. And look at the people...

49:41.094 --> 49:44.495
how they're dressed. I
think those are cowboys.

49:46.967 --> 49:48.628
- Howdy.
- Howdy.

49:48.769 --> 49:52.967
Hold up here. I got a little
business I wanna take care of.

49:53.273 --> 49:55.298
Hold on to the horses, will you?

49:59.479 --> 50:01.174
I'll be right back.

50:30.210 --> 50:31.438
Move it!

50:32.713 --> 50:35.443
- What's happening?
- We just robbed the bank!

50:35.515 --> 50:38.678
- What did you say?
- We just robbed the bank!

50:40.687 --> 50:42.621
What do you mean, "we?"

50:46.893 --> 50:48.861
The bank, they just robbed the bank!

50:48.962 --> 50:49.951
<i>Oy gevald!</i>

50:53.967 --> 50:56.435
- We need a posse, boys, let's go!
- What for?

50:56.503 --> 50:57.492
I said, we need a posse!

50:57.571 --> 50:59.539
To hell with you! I ain't
got any money in the bank.

50:59.606 --> 51:02.939
- But they robbed it!
- Well go get 'em. It's your bank.

51:03.009 --> 51:05.136
- $5 a man when we catch them !
- $5?

51:05.212 --> 51:06.679
- $7.50!
- Not worth it...

51:06.747 --> 51:08.578
- I'll go for $11.
- $10!

51:08.648 --> 51:11.583
- $11 !
- All right, you bastards...

51:11.685 --> 51:13.482
$11. Let's go!

51:34.207 --> 51:36.141
Don't get comfortable.
We can't stop here.

51:43.980 --> 51:48.212
- How could you do this to me?
- It's what I do. I'm a bank robber.

51:48.418 --> 51:52.184
- But you made me a bank robber!
- So what? You get your half.

51:52.389 --> 51:56.553
- Get out of my life!
- What?

51:58.295 --> 51:59.887
Get out of my life!

51:59.963 --> 52:02.261
Get out! I don't want you here!

52:02.532 --> 52:04.193
Get out of my life!

52:10.207 --> 52:11.196
Take it easy!

52:11.441 --> 52:14.205
Take it easy. You better cool off.

52:27.724 --> 52:29.055
Guns?

52:30.160 --> 52:32.492
You gonna shoot guns at me?

52:34.898 --> 52:35.887
Guns!

52:46.710 --> 52:50.840
- You know, you're really crazy.
- Sure I'm crazy. I'm a bank robber.

52:50.914 --> 52:52.905
Who else would rob a bank but a crazy?

52:52.983 --> 52:55.884
You, you ain't no bank robber.
All you did was hold the horses.

52:55.952 --> 52:58.216
- Think I could tell them that?
- Sure!

52:58.555 --> 52:59.902
- And would they listen?

53:00.003 --> 53:03.070
- Yeah, they'll listen.
Then they'll hang you!

53:03.593 --> 53:06.756
- And what if I gave back the money?
- You mean, your half?

53:09.199 --> 53:12.999
- Yes, I mean my half!  - First they'll
string you up by your balls...

53:13.069 --> 53:16.732
till you tell them where the other
half is, then they'll hang you!

53:21.411 --> 53:23.572
Make up your mind, pardner.

53:39.229 --> 53:40.218
<i>Oy gevald!</i>

53:41.064 --> 53:43.658
Go fast, horsie! Go fast!

53:43.934 --> 53:46.494
Wait, Tommy, wait! I'm coming.

53:53.810 --> 53:55.505
Looks like fresh tracks.

53:55.679 --> 53:58.512
They was here all
right. Here's some blood.

53:58.882 --> 54:01.373
Hey, that was me. I
knew I got that one.

54:01.918 --> 54:04.751
If you did, he sure took a
long time to start bleeding.

54:04.821 --> 54:08.279
All right, let's go, men. Let's
look for a tree for the hanging.

54:24.567 --> 54:27.127
Hey. Hey!

54:28.704 --> 54:30.262
Another river?

55:05.207 --> 55:08.904
- I wish that we could build a
bigger fire.  - Well, we can't!

55:09.378 --> 55:12.745
We're lucky to have this much.
They ain't that far behind us.

55:12.982 --> 55:16.042
By sunrise they're gonna
catch on to my dumb-ass trick.

55:17.153 --> 55:21.852
There, that ought to
warm you up. $320 each.

55:21.957 --> 55:23.049
Not bad, huh?

55:29.765 --> 55:30.959
Now ain't you something.

55:31.600 --> 55:34.228
To tell you the truth, I never
figured you's gonna take the money...

55:34.303 --> 55:36.100
tainted and all, like it is.

55:37.239 --> 55:40.640
So you're rich. What are
you gonna do with it all?

55:43.179 --> 55:46.307
When we get to the next town,
I'm going to send it back.

55:48.451 --> 55:52.285
Well, I'd be careful till
then. It's dangerous out here.

55:53.355 --> 55:55.346
Fella could get hisself robbed.

55:57.993 --> 56:00.689
I'll keep out a watch for strangers.

56:16.178 --> 56:17.645
About ready.

56:30.559 --> 56:32.959
Church over. We'd better make tracks.

56:37.066 --> 56:39.694
I figure they know pretty
much where we're at.

56:43.005 --> 56:45.565
It ain't gonna take
them too long to find us.

56:46.242 --> 56:48.574
Hold still. Hold
still, horsie. Be good.

56:48.811 --> 56:50.904
We can't really afford
such a late start.

57:00.422 --> 57:04.222
- What the hell are you doing?
- I don't ride today.

57:06.595 --> 57:08.324
What're you talking about?

57:09.131 --> 57:11.565
- Today is Saturday.
- So?

57:11.867 --> 57:15.268
- I don't ride on Saturday.
- Well, I know that. But don't tell me...

57:15.337 --> 57:18.773
- you ain't gonna ride today?
- I ain't gonna ride today.

57:19.141 --> 57:22.406
- I asked you not to tell me that!
- That's what I'm telling you.

57:22.478 --> 57:25.311
But this ain't no ordinary Saturday!

57:27.650 --> 57:31.108
Why is this Saturday different
from all other Saturdays?

57:31.387 --> 57:35.050
'Cause this Saturday, there's
a hanging-posse chasing us!

57:38.761 --> 57:42.060
I promise you. Right now, they're
doubling back to that stream.

57:42.131 --> 57:44.895
I don't ride on Saturday!

57:45.267 --> 57:48.065
Jesus! You give me the P-doodles!

57:49.872 --> 57:52.397
There ain't no Jews in
that posse, you know!

57:52.474 --> 57:55.773
They'd as soon string you up
on Saturday as any other day!

57:55.845 --> 57:59.212
They don't give a shit for your
holiday, don't you know that?

58:00.282 --> 58:02.512
Goddamned if I'm gonna walk!

58:05.421 --> 58:07.821
I've asked you not to say that.

58:14.964 --> 58:17.626
You stupid, ignorant, son of a bitch!

58:18.400 --> 58:21.198
I ain't waiting around
for that posse to find us!

58:22.738 --> 58:25.832
- I'm leaving!
- Who's asking you to stay?

58:26.141 --> 58:27.608
Good-bye!

58:37.419 --> 58:38.477
There it is.

58:57.740 --> 58:59.731
I'm gonna show you something.

59:02.578 --> 59:03.943
Look over there.

59:06.415 --> 59:08.007
You know what that is?

59:09.685 --> 59:10.674
Yes.

59:12.121 --> 59:13.110
Well?

59:16.425 --> 59:18.052
When the sun sets.

59:19.628 --> 59:21.027
Know what you are?

59:21.997 --> 59:23.726
You're a real meshigoonu.

59:27.903 --> 59:28.892
<i>Meshuggener.</i>

59:37.513 --> 59:40.846
They're coming. Damn you!

59:42.151 --> 59:43.675
- Come on.
- They're coming.

59:45.754 --> 59:47.517
Now?

59:48.991 --> 59:50.288
Not yet!

59:52.194 --> 59:53.354
Now?

59:55.831 --> 59:56.820
Not yet.

59:57.132 --> 59:58.121
Now!

01:00:12.481 --> 01:00:14.608
- Now!
- Thank God.

01:00:21.657 --> 01:00:23.249
Longest damn day of my life!

01:00:30.065 --> 01:00:32.397
That tree is a apple tree.

01:00:45.447 --> 01:00:48.814
Hot. It's hot.

01:00:57.993 --> 01:01:00.962
- Will you quit that! They ain't coming.
- How do you know?

01:01:01.030 --> 01:01:05.296
'Cause it's been four days. I'm telling
you they ain't coming. Now just relax.

01:01:06.268 --> 01:01:07.667
What's that?

01:01:10.939 --> 01:01:12.930
Them's Indians. Let's go!

01:01:14.143 --> 01:01:15.235
Go, horsie!

01:01:18.080 --> 01:01:20.571
Let's go! They ain't serving
tea, you know, you idiot!

01:01:22.351 --> 01:01:24.216
Go, horsie.

01:01:26.855 --> 01:01:28.254
Shee-it!

01:01:30.659 --> 01:01:35.358
Quick! Go quick, horse! Can't
they see that we're friends?

01:01:46.008 --> 01:01:47.873
What did they want?

01:01:51.046 --> 01:01:54.573
They wanted our horses, our
guns, our scalps, our heads.

01:01:55.684 --> 01:01:58.619
Jesus, I don't know. They wanted
our asses, that's what they wanted.

01:01:58.687 --> 01:02:00.018
But, why? What did we do?

01:02:00.289 --> 01:02:03.690
They've been shit on by white men so
long they don't ask questions no more.

01:02:04.226 --> 01:02:08.128
They wasn't painted up for one of your
bar matzavahs, I can tell you that.

01:02:08.397 --> 01:02:12.231
Oh, no. Oh, no. Oh, my God!

01:02:12.734 --> 01:02:14.224
- What's the matter?
- Oh, my God.

01:02:14.336 --> 01:02:16.065
- What's the matter?
- Oh, God!

01:02:16.338 --> 01:02:19.739
<i>- The Torah...
- Wait! Wait, damn it! Wait!</i>

01:02:22.077 --> 01:02:24.170
I ain't going with you
this time, goddamn it!

01:02:24.680 --> 01:02:26.341
- Let go!
- That was war paint...

01:02:26.415 --> 01:02:28.406
- you stupid ignoramus!
- Let go!

01:02:28.484 --> 01:02:30.611
- They won't talk, they'll just kill you!
- Will you let go?

01:02:30.686 --> 01:02:32.415
I ain't going, you son of a bitch!

01:02:32.488 --> 01:02:34.581
Who's asking you?

01:02:37.259 --> 01:02:38.749
So long, sucker!

01:02:40.596 --> 01:02:42.029
Have a nice funeral!

01:02:43.098 --> 01:02:45.066
You dumb asshole!

01:03:05.787 --> 01:03:08.620
Oh, come on, get me out of this.

01:03:08.957 --> 01:03:11.357
Oh, please, please, please.

01:03:12.094 --> 01:03:17.031
I'm your friend. I don't
wanna die. Please, God...

01:03:43.325 --> 01:03:45.088
I never did anything wrong.

01:03:47.996 --> 01:03:49.896
How did I get into this?

01:04:13.055 --> 01:04:17.856
- Who the hell are you?
- Me, rabbi...

01:04:19.394 --> 01:04:21.157
Jewish rabbi.

01:04:22.598 --> 01:04:26.728
Come from far away across big ocean.

01:04:27.269 --> 01:04:29.897
I read much books about Indians.

01:04:33.609 --> 01:04:36.237
You don't speak English very well.

01:04:44.519 --> 01:04:48.615
He's a holy man, Chief. Speaks to the
spirits every morning and every night.

01:04:48.690 --> 01:04:52.353
And he's so good and kind and
gentle, just a sweetheart of a man.

01:04:52.594 --> 01:04:55.085
Why, even when we robbed the bank
